# Component Conventions

## Server vs Client

- Default to Server Components. Only add `"use client"` when using hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs.
- Client components: `SiteNav`, `SiteBreadcrumbs`, `Share`, `Analytics`, `ViewTransitionHandler`, `TransitionLink`, `ResumeProfileChart`.

## Radix Themes + Tailwind

- Use Radix components (`Card`, `Badge`, `Text`, `Heading`, `Button`, `Flex`, `Box`, `Container`, `Section`, `Separator`) for UI elements.
- Use Tailwind for layout, spacing, and custom styling outside Radix.
- Page sections: wrap in `<Section size="2|3">` + `<Container size="4" px="4">`.

## Navigation Links

Always use `TransitionLink` from `@/components/transition-link` instead of plain `next/link` for internal links. This enables View Transitions.

## View Transition Names

When adding shared elements between list/detail pages, use `viewTransitionName` style prop:
```tsx
style={{ viewTransitionName: `${article.type}-${element}-${article.slug}` }}
```
Names MUST be unique per page. Duplicate names silently abort all transitions.

## Article Cards

`ArticleTeasers` supports `columns` prop: `2 | 3 | 4`. Default is 3. The teaser cards include view transition names for image, title, badge, and date.
